  "title": "Genesis",
  "description": "On a mission to craft the perfect play, struggling playwright Adam switches roles with his character Eve in a hopeless attempt to break through writer’s block. Genesis is a playful existential dive into love, freedom, and the stories we choose to (or not to) live in.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Moemen Gaafar<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Moemen Gaafar<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Ali Muhammad Khowaja, Kit Brooks<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Amy Dass, Harjot Bassi<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Maddy Lee<br/>",
  "website": "",
  "plain_language": "Adam is a playwriter who can’t think of what to write. He brings one of his characters, Eve, to life to help. When that doesn’t work, he asks her to write him into a play so he can create something great. This show is a playful story about love, freedom, and how we choose to live our lives.",
